    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Kali125-kilavi">itu varaivu nīṭa āṟṟāta talaivi nilaimai talaivaṟkut tōḻi kūṟi avaṉai neruṅki varaivukaṭāyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en"></p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali125">
                <l>kaṇṭava rilleṉa vulakattu ḷuṇarātār </l>
                <l>taṅkātu takaiviṉṟit tāñceyyum viṉaikaḷu </l>
                <l>ṇeñcaṟinta koṭiyavai maṟaippiṉu maṟipavar </l>
                <l>neñcattuk kuṟukiya kariyillai yākaliṉ </l>
                <l>vaṇpari naviṉṟa vayamāṉ celva </l>
                <l>naṉkatai yaṟiyiṉu nayaṉillā nāṭṭattā </l>
                <l>laṉpilai yeṉavantu kaḻaṟuva laiyakēḷ; </l>
                <l rend="space">makiḻcey tēmoḻit toyyilcū ḻiḷamulai </l>
                <l>mukiḻceya muḷkiya toṭarpava ḷuṇka </l>
                <l>ṇaviḻpaṉi yuṟaippavu nalkātu viṭuvā</l>
                <l>yimiḻtiraik koṇka koṭiyai kāṇī;</l>
                <l rend="space">ilaṅkē relvaḷai yērtaḻai taii </l>
                <l>nalañcela nalkiya toṭarpavaḷ cāayp </l>
                <l>pulantaḻap pullātu viṭuvā </l>
                <l>yilaṅkunīrc cērppa koṭiyai kāṇī;</l>
                <l rend="space">iṉmaṇic cilampiṟ ciṉmoḻi yaimpāṟ </l>
                <l>piṉṉoṭu keḻīiya taṭavara valku </l>
                <l>ṉuṇvari vāṭa vārātu viṭuvāy </l>
                <l>taṇṇan tuṟaiva takāay kāṇī; </l>
                <l rend="space">eṉavāṅku, </l>
                <l>aṉaiyaḷeṉ ṟaḷimati peruma niṉṉiṉ </l>
                <l>ṟiṟaivarai nillā vaḷaiya ḷivaṭkiṉip </l>
                <l>piṟaiyēr cuṭarnutaṟ pacalai </l>
                <l>maṟaiyac cellunī maṇantaṉai viṭiṉē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l corresp="4">Because there is no witnesses that comes close to the heart</l>
                <l>of those who know, although those who do not understand in the world, </l>
                <l>thinking “there won’t be those who see”, hide cruel acts that are known to the heart</l>
                <l corresp="1-3">among the deeds they do without restraint, out of control,</l>
                <l corresp="5">o lord with strong horses that are trained in generous motion,</l>
                <l corresp="6">by investigation that is unbiased although it knows that well,</l>
                <l corresp="7">coming to say “you are without love” I protest, lord, listen:</l>
                <l>you who let go [of her] without granting, in the attachment that embraced [her]</l>
                <l>so that the young breast surrounded by sandal paste of [her with] delightful sweet words</l>
                <l>make buds, although her kajal eyes drip loose tears,</l>
                <l corresp="8-11">o man from the sea of buzzing waves, you are cruel, see. </l>
                <l>You who let go [of her] without embrace, in the attachment that granted </l>
                <l>so that [her] beauty goes after having fixed beautiful foliage</l>
                <l>on [her with] shining beautiful bright bangles,</l>
                <l corresp="12-15">o man from the coast of shining water, you are cruel, see.</l>
                <l>You who let go [of her] without coming so that the fine lines fade</l>
                <l>of her vulva which is [like] a large snake that was joined by the five-parted</l>
                <l>[hair] with braid of [her with] few words like [the tinkling of] an anklet with pleasing gems,</l>
                <l corresp="16-19">man from the cool ghat, you are not [acting as is] befitting, see.</l>
                <l corresp="20">That is to say,</l>
                <l>saying “she is like that”, take care [of her], great man. Without you</l>
                <l>she is one with bangles that won’t stay at the limit of [her] wrists. For her now</l>
                <l>pallor secretly goes over [her] crescent moon like </l>
                <l corresp="21-24">glowing forehead, if you let go [of her] as one who had united [with her].</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
